status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"7ls9h","text":"After venipuncture, invert the tubes gently 8 to 10 times to fully mix tube anticoagulant with blood sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2pvo8","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ecaph","text":"Store the tube upright at room temperature until centrifugation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8h9sq","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1t79i","text":"Note: The tube stabilizes cell-free DNA for up to 14 days at 6 °C to 37 °C and CTCs for up to 7 days at 15 °C to 30 °C.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7g2n0","text":"Note: A swing bucket centrifuge is required. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":8,"length":12}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9vq33","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5vb3e","text":"Set centrifuge:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1a53v","text":"acceleration: 9","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7vrde","text":"deceleration: 9","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fcirh","text":"temperature: RT","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2j62l","text":"duration: 20 minutes","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ask9s","text":"speed: 300xg","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cnm68","text":"Place the cfDNA BCTs in the centrifuge. {"blocks":[{"key":"dm00e","text":"Remove the upper plasma layer and transfer to a new 15mL conical tube. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2ruuq","text":"Cap the conical tubes and return to the centrifuge. {"blocks":[{"key":"5o2pd","text":"Using a P1000, carefully aliquot plasma into 2D barcoded tubes at 500µL each.
